                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d675">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">823.001L52/85: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-01T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >September 1, 1930—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>182. My 178, September 1, noon, concluding paragraph. Mr. Leguia and Juan Leguia
                    have been taken to San Lorenzo Island. Dr. MacCornack accompanied them there on
                    account of Mr. Leguia’s condition. Dr. MacCornack is coming to see me tomorrow
                    when I shall telegraph any further details which may be of interest to the
                    Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
